# tests/hooks/fixtures/confidence.log.sample
#
# Representative iter shapes replayed by tests/hooks/pause_rate_budget.bats
# through compute_confidence to assert the auto_land=false rate stays at or
# below a pinned baseline. The fixture is part of the contract per
# cross-cutting invariant #1 in docs/upstream-harness-improvements.md.
#
# Format (pipe-separated, comments and blank lines skipped):
#   name|gate_result|diff_lines|touched_hooks|touched_claude_md|retry_count
#
# Coverage rationale:
#   - Happy paths exercise the HIGH branch under representative diff sizes
#     up to and including the 500-line threshold edge.
#   - One iter per single downgrade axis pins the axis as a downgrade
#     trigger (catches accidental retirement).
#   - Threshold-edge iters (500 stays HIGH, 501 downgrades) bracket the
#     diff_lines cut so a `>` vs `>=` flip surfaces here.
#   - Two-axis combinations exercise the LOW collapse so the floor is
#     visible to the rate calculation.
#
# Why a fixed fixture: a threshold-tightening change (e.g., diff>500 →
# diff>200) silently pushes recorded iters into downgrade and ramps the
# auto_land=false rate. The fixture is the bind — its rate is the budget
# any future axis change must stay within (or pay for with a retirement /
# threshold-raise documented in the back-port doc).
clean-small|PASS|100|false|false|0
clean-100|PASS|100|false|false|0
clean-200|PASS|200|false|false|0
clean-300|PASS|300|false|false|0
clean-400|PASS|400|false|false|0
clean-edge-500|PASS|500|false|false|0
clean-450|PASS|450|false|false|0
clean-50|PASS|50|false|false|0
gate-fail|FAIL|100|false|false|0
big-diff-edge-501|PASS|501|false|false|0
big-diff-1000|PASS|1000|false|false|0
touched-hooks|PASS|100|true|false|0
touched-claude-md|PASS|100|false|true|0
retry-once|PASS|100|false|false|1
two-axes-diff-hooks|PASS|1000|true|false|0
